headline: US Stock Market Today: S&P 500 Futures Fall As Rising Yields Pressure Tech
summary: The Morning Bull - US Market Morning Update Friday, Jan, 30 2026 US stock futures are pointing lower this morning, with S&P 500 contracts down about 0.8% and Nasdaq 100 futures off nearly 1%, as investors weigh a jump in the 10 year Treasury yield above 4.27% and fresh signals from overseas. Taiwan’s Q4 GDP grew 12.68% year on year, driven by AI related tech exports, which underlines how tied US chip and growth stocks are to global demand.
